The NPD Group has released its latest report detailing sales data for video games in the United States. The report shows that spending across video game hardware, software, accessories, and game cards grew 26% compared to the same period last year. Year-to-date spending increased by 17%. Across all platforms, the most popular video game in August 2018 was Madden NFL 19, with other high-ranking titles including Grand Theft Auto V, Monster Hunter: World, and Rainbow Six: Siege. Nintendo hardware unit and dollar sales are at the highest year-to-date totals since 2011, although Sonyâ€™s PlayStation 4 remains the best-selling console hardware platform in both units sold and revenue. The best-selling video games for August 2018 across popular platforms are shown below.